        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>synthetic inorganic blue pigment [300013238], blue pigment [300013182], pigment by color [300013134], pigments [300013109], colorant (material) [300013026], materials by function [300014692], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A kind of pigment of that is blue, light blue, bluish green, or green, usually prepared by adding chalk or whiting to a solution of nitrate of copper, or to ground azurite (blue) or malachite (green). Primarily used in making crayons and watercolors.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000034991/Random House Dictionary of the English Language (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Un tipo de pigmento azul, azul claro, verde azuloso o verde, generalmente se prepara al agregar tiza o un blanqueador a una solución de nitrato de cobre, a una base de azurita (azul) o malaquita (verde). Principalmente empleado en la fabricación de crayones y acuarelas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een pigmentsoort die blauw, lichtblauw, blauwachtig groen of groen is, meestal gemaakt door kalk of een bleekmiddel toe te voegen aan een oplossing van kopernitraat of aan gemalen azuriet (blauw) of malachiet (groen). Hoofdzakelijk gebruikt bij de productie van potloden en waterverf.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種呈藍色、淺藍、藍綠或綠色的顏料，通常在硝酸銅溶液或磨碎的藍銅礦（藍）或孔雀石（綠）中加入白堊或白堊粉調製而成。主要用途為製作蠟筆和水彩。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
